lzh_formatted:
  title: 北征
  author: 柳淑
  language: lzh
  text: 朔雪關西路。熊羆百萬兵。將軍出塞曲。已是大平聲。
korean:
  title: 계묘년 겨울에 북정
  author: 유숙
  language: kor
  text: |-
    눈보라 치는 관서 길에
    곰과 호랑이 같은 백만 병일세
    장군의 출새하는 군악 소리
    이것이 이미 태평의 소식일세
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_010_0470&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Northern Expedition
  author: Yu Suk
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Snowstorms sweep across the western passes,
    A million soldiers fierce as bears and tigers.
    The general's battle horns sound at the frontier—
    Already this heralds the song of great peace.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The 'western passes' (關西) refer to the strategic mountain passes west of Chang'an, a traditional frontier region in Chinese geography and poetry.
  - key: ''
    value: Bears and tigers are classical metaphors for military strength and ferocity in East Asian poetry.
  - key: ''
    value: The 'song of great peace' (太平聲) suggests that military strength and vigilance at the borders ensure lasting peace and stability for the realm.
